  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Reducing pain is an essential factor for early mobilization after osteosynthesis of femoral
      neck fractures. Systemic opioids have side effects that might obstruct mobilization and
      induce delirium and nausea. The investigators hypothesized that wound infiltration results in
      reduction in systemic opioid usage and pain relief without side effects.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
